Vector3 calculateReferencePosition ( const Vector3 &  pos  )  [inline]

This method returns the reference position associated with the input position.

The reason that it is important to round the reference position is that if the reference position changes by less than the least accurate offset from this position, entities that are meant to be stationary will move as the reference position moves.
